This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama on United Nations Day, which is celebrated on October 24th. The proclamation highlights the importance of the United Nations in promoting peace, freedom, and dignity for all people. It emphasizes the need for international cooperation in addressing global challenges and preventing conflicts. The proclamation also acknowledges the work of the United Nations in improving the lives of vulnerable populations around the world. The article concludes with a call to honor the values and principles of the United Nations and to recognize the interconnectedness of nations in working towards a more peaceful and just world.